  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Formation of the Imperative",
      "titleArabic": "صيغة الأمر",
      "content": [
        "The imperative (الأمر) is formed from the present tense (المضارع) by removing the present tense prefix and adding hamzat al-wasl at the beginning if needed.",
        "The formation follows specific rules based on the vowel pattern of the mudāri' verb."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Remove the prefix (ت/ي/أ/ن) from the mudāri'",
        "If the remaining form starts with sukūn, add همزة الوصل",
        "The vowel of hamzat al-wasl depends on the verb's pattern",
        "Use kasrah if the middle vowel is kasrah or fathah (اِفْعَلْ)",
        "Use dammah if the middle vowel is dammah (اُفْعُلْ)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "يَذْهَبُ → اِذْهَبْ", "english": "he goes → Go!" },
        { "arabic": "يَكْتُبُ → اُكْتُبْ", "english": "he writes → Write!" },
        { "arabic": "يَقْرَأُ → اِقْرَأْ", "english": "he reads → Read!" },
        { "arabic": "يَجْلِسُ → اِجْلِسْ", "english": "he sits → Sit!" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Imperative for Different Persons",
      "titleArabic": "الأمر مع الضمائر",
      "content": [
        "The imperative has different forms for masculine, feminine, dual, and plural addressees."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Masculine singular: اِفْعَلْ (ending with sukūn)",
        "Feminine singular: اِفْعَلِي (ending with ي)",
        "Masculine plural: اِفْعَلُوا (ending with وا)",
        "Feminine plural: اِفْعَلْنَ (ending with نَ)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "اِذْهَبْ", "english": "Go! (to one male)" },
        { "arabic": "اِذْهَبِي", "english": "Go! (to one female)" },
        { "arabic": "اِذْهَبُوا", "english": "Go! (to males)" }
      ]
    }
  ],
